<paragraph blockId="19.[189,455,1139,1201]" box="[189,455,1174,1201]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
BODY LENGTH. 
<quantity box="[357,450,1174,1201]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="5.4">5.4 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1399,1240,1408]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
HEAD. Head wider than long. Integument black, except part of mandibles dark reddish-brown. Face sparsely covered with long, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[778,875,1276,1302]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[189,1399,523,1894]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Scrapter oubergensis Kuhlmann sp. nov., ♀, holotype (RCMK). A. Lateral view. B. Head. C. Scutum and scutellum (dorsal view). D. Metanotum and propodeum (dorsal view). E. Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
). Clypeus slightly convex with coarse and relatively dense (i = 1–2 d) punctation; surface between punctures superficially sculptured but shiny (
<figureCitation box="[198,297,1347,1373]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[189,1399,523,1894]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Scrapter oubergensis Kuhlmann sp. nov., ♀, holotype (RCMK). A. Lateral view. B. Head. C. Scutum and scutellum (dorsal view). D. Metanotum and propodeum (dorsal view). E. Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9B</figureCitation>
). Malar area medially narrow, almost linear. Antenna dorsally blackish-brown, ventrally yellowish-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1399,1448,1617]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
MESOSOMA. Integument black, tegula dark reddish-brown. Mesoscutal disc between punctures reticulate and slightly matt; disc sparsely (i = 1.5–2.5 d) and coarsely punctate (
<figureCitation box="[976,1066,1484,1510]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[189,1399,523,1894]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Scrapter oubergensis Kuhlmann sp. nov., ♀, holotype (RCMK). A. Lateral view. B. Head. C. Scutum and scutellum (dorsal view). D. Metanotum and propodeum (dorsal view). E. Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9C</figureCitation>
). Metanotum slightly shorter than basal area of propodeum, apically with distinct narrow carinate depression (
<figureCitation box="[1146,1241,1519,1545]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[189,1399,523,1894]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Scrapter oubergensis Kuhlmann sp. nov., ♀, holotype (RCMK). A. Lateral view. B. Head. C. Scutum and scutellum (dorsal view). D. Metanotum and propodeum (dorsal view). E. Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
). Propodeum basally broadly and coarsely carinate (
<figureCitation box="[653,750,1555,1581]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[189,1399,523,1894]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Scrapter oubergensis Kuhlmann sp. nov., ♀, holotype (RCMK). A. Lateral view. B. Head. C. Scutum and scutellum (dorsal view). D. Metanotum and propodeum (dorsal view). E. Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9D</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutum, scutellum, metanotum, mesepisternum and propodeum sparsely covered with short, greyish, erect hair (
<figureCitation box="[943,1038,1590,1616]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[189,1399,523,1894]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Scrapter oubergensis Kuhlmann sp. nov., ♀, holotype (RCMK). A. Lateral view. B. Head. C. Scutum and scutellum (dorsal view). D. Metanotum and propodeum (dorsal view). E. Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,888,1656,1683]" box="[189,888,1656,1683]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">WINGS. Yellowish-brown; wing venation and stigma brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1246,1722,1748]" box="[189,1246,1722,1748]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">LEGS. Integument black. Vestiture greyish-brown; scopa greyish-white, dorsally brownish.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1399,1787,2027]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
METASOMA. Integument black, apical margins of terga narrowly black to translucent dark reddish-brown (
<figureCitation box="[198,291,1823,1849]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[189,1399,523,1894]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Scrapter oubergensis Kuhlmann sp. nov., ♀, holotype (RCMK). A. Lateral view. B. Head. C. Scutum and scutellum (dorsal view). D. Metanotum and propodeum (dorsal view). E. Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
). Disc of T1 without hair; following terga with very short but increasingly more and longer hair; apical tergal hair bands missing on all terga (
<figureCitation box="[776,867,1858,1885]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[189,1399,523,1894]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Scrapter oubergensis Kuhlmann sp. nov., ♀, holotype (RCMK). A. Lateral view. B. Head. C. Scutum and scutellum (dorsal view). D. Metanotum and propodeum (dorsal view). E. Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
); prepygidial and pygidial fimbriae relatively short, blackish-brown. T1 finely and densely (i = d) punctate, between punctures smooth and shiny; T2– T4 slightly coarser punctate; T2 between punctures basally superficially reticulate but shiny, apically smooth; T3–T4 between punctures superficially reticulate and slightly matt; T2–T4 with polished to superficially sculptured, but shiny apical tergal depression (
<figureCitation box="[886,978,2001,2027]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[189,1399,523,1893]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[189,1399,523,1894]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 9. Scrapter oubergensis Kuhlmann sp. nov., ♀, holotype (RCMK). A. Lateral view. B. Head. C. Scutum and scutellum (dorsal view). D. Metanotum and propodeum (dorsal view). E. Metasoma (dorsal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3836070" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3836070/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
